# Keeps the Next.js `public/` directory tracked in git.
#
# The production Dockerfile (runner stage) runs:
#     COPY --from=builder /app/public ./public
# Next.js standalone output (`output: "standalone"`) does NOT emit a public/
# directory — static assets in public/ must be copied separately. Without this
# directory existing in the repo, `docker compose build app` fails at that COPY
# with: "/app/public": not found — which aborts the first VPS deploy.
#
# Drop real static assets (favicon, og images, robots.txt, etc.) here as needed.
